					<head>Karaite commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>An Arabic commentary on the books of Kings.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="320v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Commentary on the books of Kings </title>
							<note>Contains Exodus 13:17-15:1, 15:22-17:7, 18:1-21:36, 22:4-30:21, 30:33-32:29, 33:12-34:26. Pointed and accentuated Hebrew text, with a translation and short commentary in (Judeo-)Arabic.<p>An anonymous Arabic commentary on the Kings: the pointed Hebrew text with an Arabic translation is embodied. </p>
								<p>The 'sedarim' are marked in the margins with a latter samekh. </p>
								<p>The readings of the קרי are given in the margin. </p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">נגמר פרוש ספר מלכים "בעזרת מלך מלכים" ב<date when="1619" calendar="Hebrew">יום רביעי בשבוע ובוא שנים עשר בחדש אדר שנת חמשת אלפים ושלש מאות ושבעים ותשעה שנים לבריאת העולם</date> ושלום. וכתב אתו הע' הצ' <name type="person" role="scribe">יוסף ברכה</name> השם ירפא חלוי ויחבוש שברו" אמן.<locus n="320v"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>320 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>207</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>180</height>
										<width>110</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>320 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>32 quires, nos. 1-12, 14-33, of mostly 10 laeves each. Quire no. 34 has only 3 leaves. </p>
									<p>Signatures in Hebrew letters and Arabic words on the upper margin of the first page of a quire, and in Hebrew letters at the ends of the quires. </p>
									<p>Missing quire no. 13. </p>
									<p>Quires 1, 17, 23, 32 are defective. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Gaps after folios: 6, 118, 152, 210 and 294. </p>
									<p>Some margins slightly water-damaged. </p>
									<p>Folios 283-294 partly damaged and/or stained. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="21" writtenLines="21">
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>The Hebrew text is punctuated.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Semi-cursive script of the 19th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Yosef Berakhah</name>: inscribed in the colophon, folio 320v. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p/>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Elḥakhim ben Avraham</name>: inscribed in a note, folio 1r.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Eli᾿av ben Avraham</name>, <name type="person" role="owner">Eli῾ezer Leṿi ben Barukh Leṿi Ḳayam</name>, <name type="person" role="owner">Yeshu῾ah Leṿi ben Shelomoh ha-Zaḳen</name>: inscribed in a note, folio 320v. </p>
							<p>The record of the last name is dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1815</date>.</p>
						</additions>
